	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>NewRisingSun</b> [ Thu Jan 11, 2018 4:11 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>SLROM with battery-backed CHR-RAM?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />While perusing the <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10611" class="postlink">leaked original Nintendo MMC1 datasheet</a> (March 26, 1987 revision), I noticed that the &quot;cassette repertoire&quot; on page two included two entries with 128/256 KiB PRG-ROM, 8 KiB CHR-RAM, and a battery that is described as backing the CHR-RAM, and this board is called &quot;SLROM&quot;. Apparently, Nintendo originally had different ideas for SLROM...

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
